[Course_Description]
Learn how to shoot professional-looking video in your own home. Get a crash course in the basics of video production, including cameras, lighting, and composition, tailored for the first-time video shooter. Instructor Ash Blodgett covers technical concepts—such as frame rate, shutter speed, aperture, and exposure—in a concise and easy-to-understand way, giving you the basic information you need to make sure your footage looks its best. She also provides tips for capturing great audio and lighting your scene without expensive equipment. Plus, learn how to make a great video using just your mobile phone. These tips and techniques are perfect for creating great video on a budget—without ever having to leave home. This course was created by Ash Blodgett. We are pleased to offer this training in our library.